        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer438093259" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10320458573095997655">I picked up this at a used bookstore - I&apos;d never read any Carson McCullers, but had heard of &quot;The Ballad of the Sad Cafe&quot;. I didn&apos;t read it right away. As it happens, the book I read just before this one was The Hunchback of Notre Dame (Notre Dame de Paris). I just think it&apos;s really weird that I ended up reading two novels, back to back, that involved hunchbacked characters and unreturned love. <br/><br/>The McCullers book I read was actually a collection of her short stories. I really enjoyed The Ballad,</span>
  <span id="freeText10320458573095997655" style="display:none">I picked up this at a used bookstore - I'd never read any Carson McCullers, but had heard of "The Ballad of the Sad Cafe". I didn't read it right away. As it happens, the book I read just before this one was The Hunchback of Notre Dame (Notre Dame de Paris). I just think it's really weird that I ended up reading two novels, back to back, that involved hunchbacked characters and unreturned love. <br /><br />The McCullers book I read was actually a collection of her short stories. I really enjoyed The Ballad, a complex bit of Southern Gothic. The other stories were rather flat.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10320458573095997655" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
